processData(number, text, flag)#

Converts a numbers, text and bool to a string and combine them to one string

Parameters:

  • number (double) – A number that must be in range [0;100]

  • text (char array) – A char array with size 1xN

  • flag (bool) – A logical value like 0, 1, true, false

Returns:

Concatenated string

Return type:

string

Example

output = processData(5, '#123', 1);
>>> ans = "5#1231"
